//precaution name Get Vaccinated! Stay At Home Wash Hands Use Masks Use Hand Sanitizer Do NOT touch your Face Avoid Contacts Avoid Crowd Places Social Distancing
//description
Ensure you are fully vaccinated including the booster shot. It is better to quarantine yourself especially if you have any sypmtoms to protect yourself and others. Wash your hands for at least 20 seconds with water and soap. If you have to leave home, always keep your mask on. Sanitize your hands before and after interacting with anything to lessen the chances of getting infected. Our hands carry a lot of germs from our day to day activities so avoid touching your face as much as possible. Avoid getting in contact with people as much as possible, avoid handshakes or hugging. Avoid going to crowded places. More people = Higher chances of infection. If you must contact people or go outside ensure to maintain social distance for your and others safety. Date of Birth: Gender: Male Female Country:
